Go to NCBI GEO and search for a Bulk RNAseq SRR of interest
Download the SRR FW i RV directly or open Galaxy (https://usegalaxy.org/) and upload - paste/fetch data and copy the FW and RV file links.
In Galaxy use Faster Download and Extract Reads in FASTQ (fasterq dump) to extract the FastQ reads
Use FastQC in Galaxy for tje read quality reports and if necessary do Trimming (fastp)
Use (salmon quant) for transcript quantification, in the module options choose paired end and use the cDNA reference annotation
Paste the generated data in the correspondent folders (see example_structure) 
Use R code to process and analyze data
